            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2220-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top the pizza with the <strong>torn mozzarella </strong>and then put the tray[s] into the oven for 13-15 min or until the cheese has melted and the base is crispy – this is your <strong>tandoori-style chicken pizza</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2220-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2220-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2220-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2220-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2220-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pizza is cooking, combine the <strong>remaining chopped garlic</strong> with your <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong>, 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and 1<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> in a bowl<strong> </strong>–<strong> </strong>this is your <strong>garlic & herb dip</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2220-step-7-x200.jpg",
